# Workflow Session Rules

## Start Project
When user says "Start Project", "Begin Project", "Start Session", or "Cold Start":
- Execute `.cursor/prompts/Start-Project.md` workflow
- Read mandatory docs in order (README.md, START-HERE.md, project-log.md, Checkpoint.md)
- Run lightweight pre-flight environment checks
- DO NOT auto-start development servers

## End Project
When user says "End Project", "End Session", "Close Session", or "Session Closeout":
- Execute `.cursor/prompts/End-Project.md` workflow
- Summarize changes, update tracking logs, run Git audits, and prompt for commits
- Clean up active listeners/ports (port 3000)

## Update Docs
When user says "update docs":
- Execute `.cursor/prompts/Update-Docs.md` workflow
- Scan, sync, and resolve any documentation inconsistencies
- Log recent fixes to ISSUES-RESOLVED.md

## Update Project
When user says "Update Project" or "Sync Project":
- Execute `.cursor/prompts/Update-Project.md` workflow
- Automatically detect git history/recent commits to sync project-log.md and Checkpoint.md

## Backup Project
When user says "backup project", "create backup", or "backup":
- Execute backup ritual in `.cursor/custom-scriptz/backup-system/CURSOR.md`
- **Use `AskQuestion` tool** for each step (clickable choices) — see `.cursor/rules/interactive-workflows.mdc`
- Do **not** use text-only "Reply 1 or 2" prompts

When user says **"backup quick"**, **"backup project quick"**, **"backup full"**, or **"backup project full"**:
- **Non-interactive** — run `npm run msc:backup:quick` or `npm run msc:backup:quick:full` immediately (no AskQuestion, no note)
- See `.cursor/rules/global.mdc`

## Push Website Live
When user says **"push website live"**, **"push it live"**, **"push site live"**, or **"deploy live"**:
- Execute `.cursor/prompts/Push-Website-Live.md` workflow
- Run `npm run push:website:live` from repo root (or `--dry-run` first if operator wants preflight only)
- Use **AskQuestion** to confirm hPanel server prep (STOP + cleanup) and restart (START) when the script reaches those gates
- Report `verify:live` and `verify:live:version` results
- See `.cursor/rules/global.mdc`
